op <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add flour, sugar, baking powder, bicarbonate of soda and salt then mix <b>15 sec\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Add butter and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>."},{"content":"Add buttermilk and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>. Tip out onto a generously floured work surface and flatten to 1.5 cm thick. Using a cookie cutter (5 cm), cut out preferred shapes of dough and place on fruit, with approx. 5 cm between each. Re-roll any trimmings to cut further shapes."},{"content":"Brush shapes lightly with buttermilk then sprinkle with Demerara sugar. Bake for 35-45 minutes (170°C) until cobbler topping is cooked and well browned."},{"content":"Serve hot - delicious with cream, custard or ice cream."}],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 20m","8 portions"]}